#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:1
msgid "Import & Export TTL"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:5
msgid "Exporting a Turtle file"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:7
msgid ""
"When you have filled in the tabs and validated the form, click **Download "
"TTL** in the bottom bar. The browser downloads a `.ttl` file named after the "
"service identifier."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:9
msgid "The exported file contains:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:11
msgid "All namespace declarations"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:12
msgid "The `cpsv:PublicService` entity and all its linked entities"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:13
msgid "Any preserved DMN blocks (if a file with DMN data was imported)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:17
msgid "Importing an existing Turtle file"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:19
msgid "Click **Import TTL File** in the header."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:20
msgid "Select a `.ttl` file from your file system."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:21
msgid "The editor parses the file and populates all tabs."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:22
msgid "A green confirmation message appears under the page title."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:24
msgid ""
"The import handles vocabulary variants gracefully — properties expressed "
"with alternative prefixes or legacy aliases are normalised to the canonical "
"form the editor uses."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:28
msgid "Round-trip editing"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:30
msgid ""
"Importing a file that was previously exported from the editor produces "
"identical output on re-export. This makes the editor suitable for "
"collaborative workflows where a file passes between multiple team members, "
"each adding or editing different sections."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:34
msgid "Importing files with DMN data"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:36
msgid ""
"If the imported Turtle file contains DMN entities (`cprmv:DecisionModel`, "
"`cpsv:Input`, `cprmv:DecisionRule`), they are automatically detected and "
"preserved."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:43
msgid ""
"The DMN tab displays a preservation notice showing what was found. The "
"preserved blocks are appended unchanged to every subsequent export — they "
"are not editable through the form interface. This protects deployed decision "
"model metadata from accidental modification during collaborative editing."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:45
msgid "**To clear the preserved DMN data and start fresh:**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:47
msgid "Click **Clear Imported DMN Data** in the DMN tab."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:48
msgid "Confirm the action in the dialog."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:49
msgid "The tab returns to normal upload mode."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:50
msgid "Upload a new `.dmn` file and proceed with the standard DMN workflow."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:54
msgid "Importing files without all sections"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cpsv-editor%5Cuser-guide%5Cimport-export-ttl.md:56
msgid ""
"A partial Turtle file — one that contains only a service and organisation, "
"for example, with no rules or parameters — imports successfully. Only the "
"sections present in the file are populated; all other tabs remain empty. You "
"can then fill in the missing sections and export the complete file."
msgstr ""
